      ],
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A pointer to the descriptor to be flattened. See ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/aedesc",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "theAEDesc"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A pointer to memory, allocated by the application, where the flattened data will be stored. See the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "bufferSize",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " parameter for information on how large a buffer you should allocate.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "buffer"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The size of the buffer pointed to by buffer. Prior to calling ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "AEFlattenDesc",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ", you call the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1447305-aesizeofflatteneddesc",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " function to determine the required size of the buffer for the flatten operation.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "If ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "bufferSize",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " is too small, ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "AEFlattenDesc",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " returns ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "errAEBufferTooSmall",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " and doesnâ€™t store any data in the buffer.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "bufferSize"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A pointer to a size variable. On return, the variable contains the actual size of the flattened data. You can specify ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "NULL",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " for this parameter if you do not care about the returned size.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "actualSize"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A result code. See ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/applicationservices/apple_event_manager#1656145",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Flattening a descriptor serializes the data it contains. That is, it reduces a complex, possibly deeply nested structure to a series of bytes that can conveniently be stored. The descriptor can be reconstituted from the stored bytes with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/1448997-aeunflattendesc",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " function.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Applications can be scriptable and work with Apple events without needing to flatten and unflatten descriptors. Flattening is a special-purpose capability that is useful in circumstances where it may be convenient to store data by saving and restoring a descriptor, rather than having to manually extract the data from it, store the data as a separate step, then manually recreate the descriptor (if necessary). For example, you might use flattening to store a preference setting received through an Apple event.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Flattening and unflattening should work without loss of data on descriptors that represent ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "AEDesc",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "AEList",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "AERecord",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " structures. You can also use the process with ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "AppleEvent",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " descriptors. However, keep in mind that Apple events may contain attributes that are relevant only to a running process, and these attributes may not keep their meaning when the event is reconstituted.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Flattening and unflattening works across OS versions, including between Mac OS 9 and macOS.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Flattening is endian-neutral. That is, you can save flattened data on a machine that is either big-endian or little-endian, then retrieve and unflatten the data on either type of machine, without any special steps by your application.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "1770222",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Version-Notes",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Thread safe starting in OS X v10.2.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
